Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.08,0:00:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut cases are even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.58,0:00:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.59,0:00:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is the mansion solution!\NThere's more than just a code here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.86,0:00:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.63,0:00:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.65,0:00:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.96,0:02:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old guy received a letter from\Nsomeone named Nakamura Misao,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.97,0:02:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,asking him to solve the strange\Nmysteries of an inherited mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.60,0:02:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mansion really\Nwas full of mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.56,0:02:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One handrail post by the front\Ndoor had a tiger sculpture on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.07,0:02:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other post had strange holes in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.82,0:02:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The house was filled with clocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.53,0:02:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One clock had had\Nsomething removed from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.04,0:02:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At exactly 11:00, all the\Ndigital clocks in the house rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.08,0:02:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The VCR's timer was\Nset for exactly one minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.84,0:02:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the digital clocks\Nhad a crack in the same spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.84,0:02:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It all seems to have been\Nset up to convey something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.39,0:02:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, someone\Nseemed to be hiding in the attic!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.10,0:02:53.73,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,File 'Goblin'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.27,0:02:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ln the desk was a file filled \Nwith newspaper clippings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.78,0:03:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about the Goblins, a bandit gang that\Nhad disappeared ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.49,0:03:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Demon, the name of the Goblins'\Nleader, was found on a golf bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.45,0:03:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even stranger was\Nthe mirror affixed to the desk
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.04,0:03:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the hole in the wall\Ndirectly below the cuckoo clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.38,0:03:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what came out of\Nthe cuckoo clock at 1:10...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.30,0:03:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...were ghastly goblin figures!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the key to\Nsolving these mysteries?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.06,0:03:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Case of the Mysterious\NBandit Mansion (Part 2)."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.78,0:03:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Demon figures from the cuckoo clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.28,0:03:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Demons aren't animals!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.66,0:03:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are such creepy things doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.41,0:03:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those aren't just demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.33,0:03:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're definitely the goblin figures
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.17,0:03:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Bandits of the Wind\Nused to leave behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.00,0:03:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why three of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.42,0:04:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's it! That's the\Nweird thing I saw the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.68,0:04:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.97,0:04:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.60,0:04:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are letters on each of their heads!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.77,0:04:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! What are these?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.44,0:04:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The far right demon has "R"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.16,0:04:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The middle one has "N"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.20,0:04:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the left demon has "L"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.42,0:04:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the "L" and "R" mean "left" and "right,"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.17,0:04:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what does the "N" in the middle mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.05,0:04:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,North?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.43,0:04:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.48,0:05:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did those demons start crying out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.24,0:05:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At exactly 1:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.49,0:05:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1:10... That's another "110"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.99,0:05:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.33,0:05:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I saw those earlier, it was at 10:50!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.50,0:05:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not 1:10, but 10:50?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.80,0:05:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.18,0:05:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Don't tell me those figures were...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.68,0:05:36.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those figures?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.85,0:05:38.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.60,0:05:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.40,0:05:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.07,0:05:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see what's going on here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.29,0:05:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I still can't figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.25,0:06:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what these strange signs and\Ntricks Monjiro-{\i1}san {\i0}left behind mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.42,0:06:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The digital clocks and\NVCR all went off at 11:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.97,0:06:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The significant marks on\Nall of the digital clocks' panels...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.64,0:06:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cuckoo clock that\Nsuddenly went off at 1:10...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.81,0:06:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the three goblins\Nthat came out of the clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.19,0:06:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and the L, N, and R that\Nwere engraved on their foreheads...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.99,0:06:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the key to answering\Nall these mysteries?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.33,0:06:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.45,0:06:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.33,0:06:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you notice it while looking\Nfor animals around the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.71,0:06:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought something was missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A lion!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.34,0:06:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't see any at all! They should\Nbe really easy to design, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.59,0:06:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid! There were\Ntwo big lions on the front door!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.93,0:06:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? There were?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.23,0:07:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, if he collected all\Nthese animals, he wouldn't forget lions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.44,0:07:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lion is the king of the animals!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.53,0:07:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,King?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.49,0:07:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.20,0:07:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.75,0:07:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing! I just remembered\Nsomething funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.79,0:07:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.88,0:07:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm right,\Nit's truly a unique code!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.84,0:07:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, the letter O or the number 0\Nshould've come out of the clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.10,0:07:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But L, N, and R came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.23,0:07:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could the cuckoo clock's code\Nbe separate from the digital clocks'?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.20,0:07:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.87,0:08:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1:10... 110...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.87,0:08:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The L, N, and R on their heads...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.75,0:08:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A trio of goblins...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.25,0:08:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trio... Three...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.59,0:08:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Triplets... Triplets?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.76,0:08:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The L, N, and R are triplets!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.76,0:08:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.14,0:08:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.14,0:08:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.11,0:08:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! I've got it completely figured out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.49,0:08:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}? Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.62,0:08:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.62,0:08:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh! Where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.79,0:08:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's your dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.92,0:08:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the study, still figuring out the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.72,0:08:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, it's going to get dark soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.80,0:09:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rushing won't help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.68,0:09:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.10,0:09:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer might come\Nif we think hard into the night!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.33,0:09:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.16,0:09:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The digital clocks\Nall went off at 11:00 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.25,0:09:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a crack on all the digital\Npanels after the digits "110"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.22,0:09:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the cuckoo clock\Nrang at 1:10. Another "110."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.01,0:09:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all 110!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.06,0:09:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does 110 mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.89,0:09:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it the emergency\Npolice number after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.61,0:09:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Maybe it's time\Nwe give up and go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:09:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.95,0:10:02.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would've made more sense\Nto set the digital clocks to 1:10, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.74,0:10:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.79,0:10:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Earth to Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.16,0:10:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! If you wanna\Ngo home, then go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.55,0:10:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get mad at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.39,0:10:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's late enough now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.56,0:10:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,110... 110... 11...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.56,0:10:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Stripes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.32,0:10:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"11" refers to a striped pattern!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.90,0:10:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if we check all the zebras\Nin the house, we'll find something!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.37,0:10:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But wouldn't he\Nhave chosen 11:11 instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, tigers have stripes, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.25,0:10:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There are striped cats, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.46,0:10:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, which are stronger, zebras or tigers?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.92,0:11:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Tigers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.80,0:11:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then tigers are the ♪1 animal?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.55,0:11:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lions are probably ♪1, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.14,0:11:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Lions are?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.60,0:11:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder they're\Ncalled "king of all sixty beasts"!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.19,0:11:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sixty?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.61,0:11:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're dumb. They're \N"king of all 100 beasts."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.57,0:11:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[In Japanese, "100 beasts" sounds like "110,"]\NKing of 100 beasts?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.15,0:11:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,[and "king" sounds like the letter "O."]\NEh? King of 110?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.58,0:11:27.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,King of all 100 Beasts' [110 + O]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.79,0:11:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! I've figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.16,0:11:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This "1100" is a code referring\Nto the king of all the beasts: the lion!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.26,0:11:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mark between the zeroes
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.30,0:11:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was trying to tell us to think\Nof them as separate words!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.18,0:11:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Checking the lions\Nwill solve this mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.48,0:11:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But I don't see any lions...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.98,0:11:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monjiro-{\i1}san {\i0}probably got rid\Nof all unrelated lions in the house
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.82,0:12:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep them from distracting us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.41,0:12:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why some things\Nseemed broken or scraped away!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.28,0:12:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.87,0:12:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then are the lions in question\Nthe ones on the front door?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.96,0:12:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! We should find something\Nif we check them out!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.17,0:12:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing seems strange about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.30,0:12:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.35,0:12:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, how do you\Nexplain that cuckoo clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.85,0:12:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"King" in Japanese\Nstarts with the letter "O."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.69,0:12:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-True. "LNR" doesn't\Nfit with the "king" thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.86,0:12:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it have meant something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.03,0:12:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That only appeared in the cuckoo clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.49,0:12:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't out of the question...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.70,0:12:57.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but then what? Is there\Nyet another way to read 110?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.71,0:13:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 1:10, so if you split the 1 and 10...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.71,0:13:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One, "i," ten, "to"...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.55,0:13:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One, ten... One, "to"... "Hi," "to"...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.14,0:13:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hitou? [secluded hot spring]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.14,0:13:11.72,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hitou
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:13.56,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Ito
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ito? [thread]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.98,0:13:15.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Itou
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.98,0:13:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ltou? [person's name]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.44,0:13:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Itou!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.65,0:13:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Monjiro-{\i1}san {\i0}know\Nanyone named "Itou-{\i1}san{\i0}"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.57,0:13:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.40,0:13:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about a\NNaitou-{\i1}san {\i0}or a Saitou-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.24,0:13:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.28,0:13:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's neat! Changing the first letter\Nmakes completely different names!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.08,0:13:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so neat about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.42,0:13:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, those\Ngoblins had letters on their heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.17,0:13:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They all looked the same, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.18,0:13:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The L, N, and R on their heads...\NAnd they looked the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.39,0:14:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three similar words that start\Nwith L, N, and R, followed by 110?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.03,0:14:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.86,0:14:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.20,0:14:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cuckoo clock code was saying\Nto put L, N, and R before "ight"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.87,0:14:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was saying, "Light! Night! Right!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.80,0:14:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something will happen if we shine\Na light on the right lion at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.64,0:14:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you just shone light on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.64,0:14:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.31,0:14:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.86,0:14:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? Right behind the right lion!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.78,0:14:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.78,0:14:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not very obvious,\Nbut it looks like it opens up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.08,0:15:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It does!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.13,0:15:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! If you shine the light through here--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.88,0:15:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.22,0:15:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This is--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.64,0:15:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ran. Close the door\Nand shine the light through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.47,0:15:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.73,0:15:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The light is reflecting!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.53,0:15:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! There's a mirror in the post!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.20,0:15:34.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just follow the light!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.75,0:15:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It goes inside the mansion\Nthrough a hole in the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.21,0:15:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the hole in the study!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.18,0:15:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! To the study!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.22,0:15:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find anything?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.31,0:16:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just keep shining the\Nlight with the door closed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.85,0:16:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Still?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.53,0:16:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.16,0:16:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bird this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.59,0:16:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.30,0:16:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The light from outside\Nreflects off the mirror on the desk
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.26,0:16:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and shines on the\Ncuckoo clock from below.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.30,0:16:39.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a photometer inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.10,0:16:39.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Photometer = light detector
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.56,0:16:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be set up to only work\Nat night, so the sun won't set it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.56,0:16:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something on the bird...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.61,0:16:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A wristwatch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! That must be a present\Nour grandfather left for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.70,0:17:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sure is fancy, though!\NIt's covered with gems!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.08,0:17:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If these are premium jewels,\Nit could be worth billions of yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.63,0:17:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! After all...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.13,0:17:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it's probably a stolen item that\NDemon, the leader of the Goblins,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.34,0:17:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,secretly held on to!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.47,0:17:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Demon, the leader of the Goblins?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.14,0:17:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who\Nlived here: Monjiro-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.77,0:17:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The figures that came\Nout of the cuckoo clock
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.98,0:17:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,looked just like the goblin figures\Nthe bandit gang always left behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.03,0:17:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it looks like he received a\Ngolf bag with the alias "Demon" on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.90,0:17:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't think either of them are\Nthe Misao-{\i1}san {\i0}who sent the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.95,0:17:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the letter said this:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.96,0:17:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I haven't been here long\Nand don't know the house well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.00,0:17:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured I wouldn't\Ndiscover anything on my own."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, they knew how to open the old door,\Nand they live here together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.76,0:18:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, he thought the cuckoo\Ncame out at 10:50 instead of 1:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.72,0:18:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is because he\Ndidn't see the clock directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.02,0:18:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead, he looked through the hole\Nand saw the clock in the mirror!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.03,0:18:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, when Misao-{\i1}san {\i0}mentioned\Nbeing watched by someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.70,0:18:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that was referring to these two!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.54,0:18:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I think\NMisao-{\i1}san {\i0}is a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.00,0:18:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.29,0:18:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here! Look at the\Nstamp on this letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.42,0:18:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See the lipstick on the underside?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.43,0:18:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! She licked it\Nwhen sticking it on here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.51,0:18:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure you had\Nthis all figured out already!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.23,0:18:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uhh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, does that mean--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.90,0:18:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.57,0:19:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the remnants of the Goblins.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.49,0:19:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We came to get the last\Ntreasure our boss had held on to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.00,0:19:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Held on to?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.75,0:19:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, when we disbanded,\Nhe gave us almost everything we stole,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.92,0:19:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he kept the most\Nvaluable items all for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.55,0:19:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And those would be\Nthe jewels on this watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.39,0:19:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He finally kicked the bucket,\Nso we decided to scour this house
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.27,0:19:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he used to hole up in...\Nbut there was someone already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.56,0:19:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume it was the real Misao-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nwho's locked in the attic now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.19,0:19:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. When we tossed her\Nup there, she just kept wailing on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.28,0:19:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about how some great detective\Nwould be here soon to get us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.29,0:19:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you showed up\Nat the perfect time,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.46,0:19:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I pretended to be her to\Nhave you solve the code our boss left.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.34,0:20:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now hand over the watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.59,0:20:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hand it over quietly and I won't kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.22,0:20:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.35,0:20:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.36,0:20:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.11,0:20:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move! Move and I snap her neck!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.74,0:20:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.20,0:20:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.17,0:20:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A heel drop...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.38,0:20:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That scared me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.93,0:20:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It did?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.18,0:20:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's contact the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.69,0:22:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After we contacted them,\Nthe local police rushed to the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.45,0:22:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still knocked out, the criminal\Nduo was carried into ambulances,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.41,0:22:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Misao-{\i1}san {\i0}was rescued\Nfrom the attic, safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.37,0:22:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought, she was the\Ngirl in the photo with Monjiro-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.50,0:22:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.75,0:22:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this was in the cuckoo clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.09,0:22:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monjiro-{\i1}san {\i0}probably made\Nthe watch for you out of stolen jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.93,0:22:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody will know about\Nit if you don't say anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.60,0:23:01.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But stolen goods are\Nstolen goods. I can't accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.65,0:23:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, my grandfather\Nhas already given me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.69,0:23:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something more valuable than jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.73,0:23:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.57,0:23:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mysteries scattered about this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.99,0:23:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For a mystery writer like me,\Nit's the greatest present!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.83,0:23:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.16,0:23:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, it's a waste...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.58,0:23:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.34,0:23:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows, maybe it was\Nactually meant for whoever found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.88,0:23:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's for me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.97,0:23:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.10,0:23:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so, old guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.93,0:23:44.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was most definitely a watch\NMonjiro-{\i1}san {\i0}made for Misao-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.73,0:23:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look closely at the watch face.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.78,0:23:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's stopped at 3:30.\N330 can be read as "Misao."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.27,0:24:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakai-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.80,0:24:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's--!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.14,0:24:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.76,0:24:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Scoop Photograph Murder Case."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.32,0:24:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.04,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Express bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.86,0:24:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode's case is about a scoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.46,0:24:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that person next \Nto you in the photo, dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.34,0:24:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.77,0:24:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
